ğŸ§© 2ï¸âƒ£ Namespace
ğŸ“˜ Definition
A Namespace in Kubernetes/OpenShift is a logical isolation boundary within a cluster â€” used to separate and group resources like Pods, Services, and Deployments.
Itâ€™s like a virtual cluster inside your cluster.

ğŸ” Key Points
Used to separate workloads and teams logically.
Provides resource isolation (via quotas, limits, and RBAC).
Each namespace has its own network space, so pods in different namespaces can be restricted from talking to each other via NetworkPolicies.
Some namespaces are system-reserved, like:
default â€” default workspace for users.
kube-system â€” for system pods.
openshift-* â€” for internal OpenShift components.

ğŸ“Š Example
